The paper deals with mining individual mobile phone user behavior using time-series data. This falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves analyzing user behavior patterns. Additionally, the paper proposes a new segmentation technique (BOTS) that takes into account the number of incidences of diverse behaviors dynamically, which involves data mining and machine learning techniques (cs.CY, cs.SD). The paper also discusses the importance of considering individual user behavior, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing and processing large datasets, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB).
